JAX-RS is the Java specification for REST web services provided under JSR-311. 

Basically, it provides annotations for different functionalities. 
Following 11 annotations provided under JAX_RS. 
@PATH
@HEAD
@GET
@POST
@PUT
@DELETE
@PRODUCES
@CONSUMES
@PATHPARAM
@QUERYPARAM
@PROVIDER

JAX-RS exception handling with Jersey2.0. 
link: https://dennis-xlc.gitbooks.io/restful-java-with-jax-rs-2-0-en/cn/part1/chapter7/exception_handling.html

Above link provides specific details about the HTTP status codes and explanation about the same. 


Exception thrown: 

Status Code: 415 - Unsupported Media Type (NotSupportedException) ::
Example: This occurs if the web service only consumes JSON file (@Consumes({MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON})).
And the client is sending XML instead of JSON data. 

